snd-hda-codec-cs8409-imac (1.11) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Speakers: fix the ASP1 bit-clock setup. ASP1_CLK_CTRL1 (coef 0x03) and
    ASP1_CLK_CTRL3 (coef 0x05) must be written wholesale (0x8000 / 0x0001) as
    in the macOS sequence; the previous read-OR-modify left stale bits
    (0x801f / 0x0260), giving the amps a malformed clock.

 -- Peter Shev <peter@shev.it>  Thu, 18 Jun 2026 18:55:00 +0000

snd-hda-codec-cs8409-imac (1.10) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Internal speakers, Phase 1. Re-enable the ASP1 speaker pins (0x24/0x25),
    widen the GPIO mask to include the amp-enable line (GPIO4), and program the
    four TAS5764 amplifiers (I2C 0xd8/0xda/0xdc/0xde, TDM channels 0/2/1/3) plus
    the CS8409 ASP1 4-channel TDM transmit path. Adds an unpaged amp-I2C write
    helper. Speakers are exposed as a manually-selectable output alongside the
    headphone; amps are programmed/enabled at init.

