snd-hda-codec-cs8409-imac (1.7) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Make the headphone a no-presence (phantom) jack by setting the NO_PRESENCE
    misc bit in its pin default config (0x002b4020 -> 0x002b4120). The jack now
    reports always-present, so WirePlumber activates the analog output profile
    automatically instead of leaving PipeWire on a Dummy sink. Supersedes the
    1.6 hp_jack_in approach, which didn't reach the ALSA jack control.

 -- Peter Shev <peter@shev.it>  Thu, 18 Jun 2026 17:05:00 +0000

snd-hda-codec-cs8409-imac (1.6) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Report the headphone jack as always present so PipeWire/WirePlumber keeps a
    usable output sink instead of falling back to Dummy Output. The reused
    CS42L42 detection mis-reads the iMac's inverted jack circuit; since the
    headphone is the only analog output, a fixed-present port is the pragmatic
    fix. Mic detection is left intact.

 -- Peter Shev <peter@shev.it>  Thu, 18 Jun 2026 16:45:00 +0000

snd-hda-codec-cs8409-imac (1.5) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Power up the CS42L83 headphone output stage at playback. The boot value of
    PWR_CTL1 (0x1101=0xfe) leaves HP/MIXER/ASP-in powered down; the playback
    hook now walks it 0xfe -> 0x9e -> 0x96 (ASP_DAI+MIXER on, wait power-good,
    then HP on), matching the macOS output enable. This was the silence cause.

 -- Peter Shev <peter@shev.it>  Thu, 18 Jun 2026 16:20:00 +0000

